Welcome to today’s episode of Nightly Nuggets – a new series from our kitchens to yours. While you’re at home, we thought we’d share some creative ways to change up your dinner routine with some of our favorite 
Chick-fil-A items. From our Chick-fil-A family to yours, let’s come together around this delicious recipe from one member of our Field Operations team, Mandy Dawkins and her kids Wyatt and Conoly – Chick-fil-A Chicken Tetrazzini! 
Ingredients:
1 12 count Chick-fil-A Grilled or Original Nuggets, chopped
½ package spaghetti noodles
¼ cup butter
1 medium onion, diced
1 tsp minced garlic
1 tsp dried basil
4-7 oz canned mushroom slices (depending on how much you like mushrooms) 
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
1 cup shredded Monterey jack cheese
1 cup sour cream
1/3 cup milk
½ cup Parmesan cheese 
Directions:
Wash hands for 20 seconds using soap and warm water. For best quality, use chicken immediately 
after purchase. If not using chicken immediately, pop in the fridge as soon as possible after purchase and remove once ready for prep. 
1. Preheat oven to 350. 
2. In a large pot of boiling water, cook spaghetti noodles and set aside. 
3. In a medium saucepan, sauté onions in butter. Add garlic, dried basil and Chick-fil-A Chicken 
Nuggets. Cook over medium heat until chicken is heated through.
4. Mix all remaining ingredients except the Parmesan cheese. 
5. Place in greased 13x9 casserole dish and top with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 30-45 minutes (or 
until bubbly and cheese is melted). Enjoy!

Welcome to today’s episode of Nightly Nuggets – a new series from our kitchens to yours. While you’re at home, we thought we’d share some creative ways to change up your dinner routine with some of our favorite 
Chick-fil-A items. From our Chick-fil-A family to yours, let’s come together around this delicious recipe from one member of our Enterprise Analytics team, Yazmin Johnson – Smoky Backyard BBQ Potato Salad! 
Ingredients:
2 cups diced red potatoes, cooked, cooled and cut into bite sized pieces
2 boiled eggs, chopped 
2-3 Tbl. sweet pickle relish or dill pickle relish 
¼ cup Chick-fil-A Sauce 
1 Tbl. mayonnaise 
celery & green onion, to taste
salt & pepper, to taste
paprika, garnish
optional: 2-3 strips bacon, cooked until crisp and chopped/crumbled 
Directions:
Wash hands for 20 seconds using soap and warm water. 
1. In a bowl, mix together Chick-fil-A sauce, relish, mayonnaise, salt, and pepper.
2. Add diced potatoes, eggs, onion, celery, and bacon (if using). Mix until well incorporated. 
3. Garnish with green onion and paprika before serving (optional). Serve immediately or chill in the 
refrigerator for a few hours or overnight. Enjoy!

Welcome to today’s episode of Nightly Nuggets – a new series from our kitchens to yours. While you’re at home, we thought we’d share some creative ways to change up your dinner routine with some of our favorite 
Chick-fil-A items. From our Chick-fil-A family to yours, let’s come together around this delicious recipe from two members of our Field Operations and International teams Priscilla and Caleb Nicholson – Deluxe 
Waffle Fries! 
Ingredients: 
3 Large Chick-fil-A Waffle Fries
1 12 count Chick-fil-A Nuggets
5 Strips of bacon, cooked and crumbled
1 Cup shredded mild cheddar cheese 
½ Cup White Queso*
1 Dollop of sour cream
3 Tablespoons diced chives 
8 oz. Tub Chick-fil-A Ranch Sauce *White Queso:
½ Cup whole milk
½ lb White American cheese, grated 
Directions:
Wash hands for 20 seconds using soap and warm water. For best quality, use chicken immediately after purchase. If not using chicken immediately, pop in the fridge as soon as possible after purchase and remove 
once ready for prep.
1. Preheat oven to 350F degrees. 
2. In a saucepan, boil milk and grated American cheese. Wisk until white queso sauce is thick. Set aside.
3. On a baking sheet, spread waffle fries evenly as base layer and add layer of nuggets and cheddar cheese. 
Repeat.
4. Top with crumbled bacon and bake in oven for 5 minutes or until cheese has melted.
5. Top with chives, ranch, white queso sauce and a dollop of sour cream. Enjoy!

Welcome to today’s episode of Nightly Nuggets – a new series from our kitchens to yours. While you’re at home, we thought we’d share some creative ways to change up your dinner routine with some of our favorite 
Chick-fil-A items. From our Chick-fil-A family to yours, let’s come together around this delicious recipe from Owner/Operator Britt Sims and her daughter Tatum – Polynesian Meatloaf! 
Ingredients:
1 lb ground turkey (may sub ground chicken) 
1 lb ground pork (if pork not available, use 2 lb ground turkey/chicken+ 1/4 C heavy whipping cream) 
1 medium onion, finely chopped 
1 medium bell pepper, finely chopped 
4 garlic cloves, finely chopped 
2 eggs 
1/3 C Chick-fil-A Polynesian Sauce 
1 C breadcrumbs 
1 Tbsp Worcestershire sauce 
2 Tbsp chopped fresh parsley (or 1 Tbsp dried) 
1.5 tsp kosher salt 
½ tsp black pepper 
½ tsp smoked paprika 
¼ tsp crushed red pepper flakes 
1/3 C Chick-fil-A Polynesian Sauce (topping) 
Directions:
Wash hands for 20 seconds using soap and warm water. 
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. 
2. Prepare a loaf pan – line with parchment or foil to overlap edges to easily remove meatloaf. 
3. In a medium mixing bowl, add all ingredients for meatloaf (not topping) & mix together until ingredients are thoroughly combined. 
4. Press into lined loaf pan and bake in center of oven for 40 minutes. 
5. After 40 minutes, spread Polynesian sauce to cover meatloaf top. Bake for 12-15 more minutes. Internal temp should be 165 or higher. 
6. Remove from oven and let cool for 5 minutes in pan. 
7. Remove from pan carefully and use reserved Polynesian drippings from pan as sauce. 
8. Delicious served diner-style with mashed potatoes & green peas. Use leftover meatloaf slices to make toasted meatloaf patty melts. Enjoy!

Welcome to today’s episode of Nightly Nuggets – a new series from our kitchens to yours. While you’re at home, we thought we’d share some creative ways to change up your dinner routine with some of our favorite Chick-fil-A items. From our Chick-fil-A family to yours, let’s come together around this delicious recipe from one member of our Culinary team Shona Jonson and her family – Spicy Bahn Mi Sandwich!

Ingredients:

Pickled Vegetables 
1/2 teaspoon salt 
1/4 cup sugar 
1/4 cup rice vinegar 
½ cup hot water 
2 Tablespoons Sweet & Spicy Siracha sauce 
1 cup cut carrots 
1 cup cut radish or daikon 
Sweet & Spicy Siracha Mayo 
1/2 cup mayonnaise 
2 Tablespoons Sweet & Spicy Siracha sauce 
Sandwich 
4 baguettes or sub rolls 
4 Chick-fil-A Spicy Filets, sliced into strips 
1-2 sliced Persian cucumbers 
Fresh cilantro 
Lime slices 
Jalapeño slices

Directions:
Wash hands for 20 seconds using soap and warm water. For best quality, use chicken immediately after purchase. If not using chicken immediately, pop in the fridge as soon as possible after purchase and remove once ready for prep. 
1. Place sliced carrots and radish into mason jar or bowl. 
2. Mix salt, sugar, rice vinegar, hot water and Sweet & Spicy Siracha sauce. Stir until sugar dissolves. 
3. Pour liquid over veggies, cover and chill in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. 
4. Mix mayonnaise and Sweet and Spicy Siracha sauce until well blended. Store in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. 
5. Once vegetables and mayo are ready, prepare sandwich toppings by first toasting baguettes, if desired.
6. Spread bread with Sweet & Spicy Siracha Mayo. 
7. Top with cucumbers, chicken, pickled veggies and cilantro. 
8. Add lime juice and/or jalapeño, if desired. Enjoy!

While you’re at home, we thought we’d share some creative ways to change up your dinner routine with some of our favorite Chick-fil-A items. From our Chick-fil-A family to yours, let’s come together around this delicious recipe from one member of our Marketing team Gillian Mauldin and kids Emery, Tait and Davis – Fruity Lemonade Frozen Pops! 
Ingredients:
1/3 - 1/2 cup fresh fruit of choice (ex. berries, kiwi, watermelon, mango-- you can mix several together)
Chick-fil-A Lemonade; enough to fill molds
Frozen pop molds 
Directions:
Wash hands for 20 seconds using soap and warm water. If not using lemonade immediately, pop in the fridge as soon as possible after purchase and remove once ready for prep. 
1. In a small bowl, add cut fruit and gently “muddle/mash” fruit. 
2. Add approx. 1-2 Tsp. of fruit to frozen pop molds (this adds texture and beautiful colors).
3. Fill molds with Chick-fil-A Lemonade. 
4. Place in freezer and allow to freeze overnight. 
5. When ready to eat, you may need to place molds in a bowl of hot water for 10-15 seconds to loosen the frozen pop. Enjoy!

Welcome to today’s episode of Nightly Nuggets – a new series from our kitchens to yours. While you’re at home, we thought we’d share some creative ways to change up your dinner routine with some of our favorite Chick-fil-A items. From our Chick-fil-A family to yours, let’s come together around this delicious recipe from one member of our Benefits team Nicole Fisher and her daughter Kennedy – Nashville Hot Nuggets! 
Ingredients:
1 T butter
1 T vegetable oil
1 tsp white sugar
2 T hot sauce (your choice)
1 tsp garlic salt
½ tsp paprika
¼ tsp cayenne pepper
1 12-count Chicken Nugget *May double recipe as needed for more servings 
Directions:
Wash hands for 20 seconds using soap and warm water. For best quality, use chicken immediately 
after purchase. If not using chicken immediately, pop in the fridge as soon as possible after purchase and remove once ready for prep. 
1. Melt butter in the microwave. 
2. Once butter is melted, transfer to a medium mixing bowl, and whisk in all oil, sugar, hot sauce, garlic salt, paprika, and cayenne pepper until smooth. 
3. Add chicken nuggets and toss to coat.
4. Serve immediately alongside Chick-fil-A Mac & Cheese and Kale Crunch. Enjoy!

Welcome to today’s episode of Nightly Nuggets – a new series from our kitchens to yours. While you’re at home, we thought we’d share some creative ways to change up your dinner routine with some of our favorite 
Chick-fil-A items. From our Chick-fil-A family to yours, let’s come together around this delicious recipe from one member of our Marketing team Jill Adams – Strawberry Shake Cake! 
Ingredients: 
1 large Chick-fil-A Strawberry Milkshake 
1 ½ cups self-rising flour 
8-10 fresh strawberries, chopped in mixer 
2 tablespoons of sugar 
1 cup heavy whipping cream 
Directions:
Wash hands for 20 seconds using soap and warm water. 
1. Preheat oven to 350F degrees.
2. In a large mixing bowl, combine Chick-fil-A Strawberry Milkshake, flour and chopped strawberries. Mix thoroughly.
3. Pour cake mixture into loaf pan.
4. Bake cake in the oven for 40 minutes.
5. Remove and let cool for 5 minutes.
6. With a hand mixer or stand mixer, combine sugar and heavy whipping cream until peaks appear.
7. Slice cake and top with whipped cream and fresh strawberries. Enjoy!
